               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the king; a few lines on the incipit page, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section of the text; elements of the punctuation signs; some other words, e.g., hale luya (e.g., fols. 2vb, 3ra, 4ra), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 9va, 18rb, 19rb), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 10rb, 10vb, 43vb), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 28rb, 28vb, 57vb), wä-tǝbl (e.g., fols. 28vb, 79rb, 80va), sälam (fol. 72rb), wä-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols. 77ra, 78rb, 79ra).</rubric>
